<subSubSection lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="497" pageId="9" pageNumber="496" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,1743,2022]" lastBlockId="10.[151,1436,150,249]" lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="497" pageId="9" pageNumber="496">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1996,2022]" pageId="9" pageNumber="496">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Klapalek" authorityYear="1922" box="[322,562,1996,2022]" class="Insecta" family="Perlidae" genus="Anacroneuria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="496" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minuta">
<emphasis box="[322,562,1996,2022]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="496">Anacroneuria minuta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was collected at Chapada dos Veadeiros and Serra dos Pireneus, and is a new record for the 
<collectingRegion box="[319,449,150,177]" country="Brazil" name="Goias" pageId="10" pageNumber="497">Goiás state</collectingRegion>
. Although previously recorded in 
<collectingRegion box="[841,962,150,176]" country="Brazil" name="Amazonas" pageId="10" pageNumber="497">Amazonas</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[976,1029,150,176]" country="Brazil" name="Para" pageId="10" pageNumber="497">Pará</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[1042,1141,150,176]" country="Brazil" name="Roraima" pageId="10" pageNumber="497">Roraima</collectingRegion>
, and 
<collectingRegion box="[1205,1313,150,176]" country="Brazil" name="Tocantins" pageId="10" pageNumber="497">Tocantins</collectingRegion>
states, the present study now expands the distribution of this species to 
<collectingRegion box="[856,985,186,213]" country="Brazil" name="Goias" pageId="10" pageNumber="497">Goiás state</collectingRegion>
. The studied specimens are typical and strongly resemble those illustrated by 
<bibRefCitation author="Froehlich, C. G." box="[578,770,222,248]" pageId="10" pageNumber="497" pagination="75 - 107" refId="ref8843" refString="Froehlich, C. G. (2002) Anacroneuria mainly from southern Brazil and northeastern Argentina (Plecoptera: Perlidae). Proceedings of the Biological Society of Washington, 115, 75 - 107." type="journal article" year="2002">Froehlich (2002)</bibRefCitation>
. The nymph was described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Ribeiro, J. M. F. &amp; Gorayeb, I. S." box="[1116,1417,222,248]" pageId="10" pageNumber="497" pagination="17 - 32" refId="ref10016" refString="Ribeiro, J. M. F. &amp; Gorayeb, I. S. (2014) Description of immatures and association with adults of three species of Anacroneuria Klapalek (Plecoptera: Perlidae) of the Brazilian Amazon. Zootaxa, 3881 (1), 17 - 32. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3881.1.2" type="journal article" year="2014">Ribeiro &amp; Gorayeb (2014)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
